<subSubSection id="1EB86555AE51FF875ACCFF3858A1F9C6" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="561D36DEAE51FF875ACCFF385FD9FEC0" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis id="64D6EACCAE51FF875ACCFF385D32FF6C" bold="true" box="[199,317,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="91A24D5DAE51FF875B4DFF395E0BFF6D" authority="M.Meshram &amp; Nikoshe, 2020" authorityName="M.Meshram &amp; Nikoshe" authorityYear="2020" box="[326,516,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flatfronta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uttara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="64D6EACCAE51FF875B4DFF395E0BFF6D" box="[326,516,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Flatfronta uttara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7FE557B7AE51FF875807FF385E6BFF6C" box="[524,612,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="91A24D5DAE51FF875930FF385F9FFF6D" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2019" box="[827,912,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flatfronta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="64D6EACCAE51FF875930FF385F9FFF6D" box="[827,912,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">F. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the characters for 
<taxonomicName id="91A24D5DAE51FF875E65FF3858CCFF6D" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2019" box="[1134,1219,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flatfronta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="64D6EACCAE51FF875E65FF3858CCFF6D" box="[1134,1219,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">F. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parenthesis) but differs as follows: 1. ventral pygofer process apex leaf like with lateral crenulate margin and reaching half length of the pygofer (pygofer process exceeding to anterior margin), 2. aedeagus sickle shaped, broad basally and narrowed apically (slender throughout with one pair of finger-like apical processes).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="561D36DEAE51FF875A9CFA7D58A1F9C6" blockId="3.[151,1437,1500,1561]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis id="64D6EACCAE51FF875A9CFA7D5CC4FA2A" bold="true" box="[151,203,1500,1525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">FIG.</emphasis>
(13–22) 
<taxonomicName id="91A24D5DAE51FF875B2EFA7D5DC0FA2B" authority="M.Meshram &amp; Nikoshe, 2020" authorityName="M.Meshram &amp; Nikoshe" authorityYear="2020" box="[293,463,1500,1524]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flatfronta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uttara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="64D6EACCAE51FF875B2EFA7D5DC0FA2B" box="[293,463,1500,1524]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Flatfronta uttara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7FE557B7AE51FF875BDFFA7C5E2DFA2B" box="[468,546,1501,1524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
13–14. Habitus dorsal, lateral; 15. Face; 16. Style 17–19. Pygofer lateral, ventral, magnified pygofer process; 20. Subgenital plate with valve; 21–22. Aedeagus dorsal, lateral with Connective.
</paragraph>
